            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Right. And it doesn't matter what command, empty or wrong or correct, you pass to `os.execute()`, it will kill nvim on the next Ctrl-C. You can use nvim as usual, as long as you don't press Ctrl-C. It seems nvim's ability to handle Ctrl-C gets busted after `:lua os.execute(\"os_cmd\")` As you said, something to do with stdin.",
